action_pairs: Ree leaves the party and sends Hayley an apology text the following morning once she's sobered up.

situation: Ryan is doing his taxes for the first time and doesn’t know what he is doing.
intention: Ryan wants to file them and get his tax return back.
action_pairs: Ryan lets his dad show him how to do them and accepts his advice.

situation: Jerry is a student and has a crush on a new student named Mary.
intention: Jerry wants to find out more about Mary.
action_pairs: Jerry visits Mary's Facebook ten times a day to collect as much info as possible on her.

situation: It is Halloween and Oliver has been invited to a friend's costume party.
intention: Oliver wants to wear a good costume.
action_pairs: Oliver dresses up as a ninja and covers his face and brings real knives to the party.

situation: Tom has the day off of work and wants to have some friends over.
intention: Tom wants to invite some friends over for drinks.
action_pairs: Tom has friends over but focuses more on playing his video game.

situation: Jacklyn drops by the store to pick up some groceries with her dog in her car.
intention: Jacklyn needs to pick up some items from the store.
action_pairs: Jacklyn orders the items from Instacart when she gets home.

situation: Mary found out her daughter is going to college and her daughter needs help finding a college.
intention: Mary wants to help pick a college for her daughter.
action_pairs: Mary picks the best school she can afford, which is a nice out-of-state, private school.

situation: Josh lives alone, but only works part time so he spends a large amount of time at his home.
intention: Josh wants to get a pet.
action_pairs: Josh gets a dog from the shelter and later starts working full time and overtime hours.

situation: Penny is the judge for an art contest her friend has entered and her friend keeps asking about what the judges are planning to do.
intention: Penny wants to spare her friend's feelings because she does not believe her friend's art is good enough.
action_pairs: Penny lets her friend know that others have submitted very good entries and the judges will probably pick one of them.

situation: Mary has some furniture she doesn't want anymore, and she knows her neighbor who doesn't have much money could use it.
intention: Mary wants to get the furniture out of her house.
action_pairs: Mary gives the furniture to her neighbor and helps them move it into their home.

situation: Tom lives with his girlfriend and doesn't have the money for take-out, but does have raw food material.
intention: Mark wants to prepare dinner.
action_pairs: Mark cooks food only for himself, and eats it.

situation: Mary is bitter about her husbands repeated infidelity when her son asks her why she is so angry with his dad.
intention: Mary wants to answer her son's question.
action_pairs: Mary tells her son about his father’s history with women in great detail.

situation: Ashley has the whole weekend off from work and has nothing planned yet.
intention: Ashley wants to see a new movie.
action_pairs: Ashley invites a group of friends to watch the new movie with her.

situation: Jeff's friend needed some money for lunch since his family has been struggling.
intention: Jeff wanted to help his friend in some way.
action_pairs: Jeff gave his friend all of the money on him and asked others for money as well.

situation: Ricky and Mark are about to order dinner at a restaurant, and Ricky offers to pay for the food.
intention: Ricky wants to eat food.
action_pairs: Ricky thanks Mark, and offers to pay for drinks and deserts.

situation: Mark is a doctor at a hospital that practices eugenics and realizes that a newly born child has dwarfism.
intention: Mark wants to decide whether the person should reproduce or not.
action_pairs: Mark decides to remove the child's testicles to prevent him from breeding and making more short people.

situation: Prentiss has just confided in Julian that he is struggling with credit card debt and asks Julian not to tell anyone else.
intention: Julian wants to help Prentiss get out of debt.
action_pairs: Julian looks up some resources on debt management and sends them to Prentiss.

situation: Josh lives at home with his parents.
intention: Josh just got home from work and wants to go to bed.
action_pairs: Josh tells his parents he's tried from working and wishes them a good night before going to bed.

situation: Gladys is turning 50 years old next month.
intention: She wants to celebrate this milestone with her best friend by flying to Ireland.
action_pairs: When they get to Ireland, Gladys is surprised to find out that her friend Gloria paid for her upgraded hotel accommodations.

situation: Joe is having dinner at a restaurant where their waiter's service is poor.
intention: Joe wants the waiter to know Joe is upset.
action_pairs: Joe complains to the waiter's manager who terminates the waiter.

situation: Ruben has plans to go out with his partner, Jenna, on New Year's Eve, but Jenna texts Ruben to say that she is feeling sick.
intention: Ruben wants to go out on New Year's Eve.
action_pairs: Ruben ignores Jenna's text and goes out for drinks with his friends instead.

situation: Jake suspects Jenny is cheating on him with another man.
intention: Jake wants to find out if his suspicions are true.
action_pairs: Jake asks Jenny if she's been seeing someone else.

situation: Maria has a very important business meeting with a client.
intention: Maria wants to attend the meeting.
action_pairs: Maria thinks showing up earlier than scheduled will make her seem prepared.

situation: Bill is at work trying to get things done and get through the day.
intention: Bill wants to finish the workday.
action_pairs: Bill focuses on the project and tries to complete it as quickly as he can.

situation: Harold plans on going to a concert and doesn't want to go alone.
intention: Harold wants to get a date.
action_pairs: Harold declines his friend's suggestion of a different race woman and tells him he is going with another pal's sister, who is his own race.

situation: Ian's brother Mike can't afford to pay the rent for his apartment and may be evicted.
intention: Ian wants to make sure that Mike has a place to live.
action_pairs: Ian gives Mike money to pay the rent.

situation: Craig has met the wife of one of his biggest clients at his work.
intention: Craig wants to see the woman again.
action_pairs: Craig invites his client's wife back to his house for drinks.

situation: Kevin has two dogs at home and needs to work some extra hours for a few weeks, wearing him out.
intention: Kevin wants to get some rest.
action_pairs: Kevin puts his dogs on a long leash and goes straight inside from work to rest, ignoring the dogs.

situation: Jake is playing against his biggest rival in football and gets in position for a tackle.
intention: Jake wants to stop the play and get possession to his team.
action_pairs: Jake tackles his foe hard and checks on him when he notices the rival seeming hurt.

situation: Claire is sitting in a lawn chair on her patio while she watches a couple get out of a van and begin moving into a nearby apartment.
intention: Claire wants to remain in her lawn chair.
action_pairs: Claire warmly greets the new couple but says that she has a bad back and cannot get up to help them move.

situation: Karen is relaxing at home watching TV when her friend Phyllis calls her to come over and play cards while she watches her kids.
intention: Karen wants to decline the request.
action_pairs: Karen tells Phyllis that her kids are really annoying, and she hates them and doesn't want to be around them.

situation: Frank is having an argument with John who is a different race while they are at work.
intention: Frank wants to say something to John during the argument.
action_pairs: Frank argues his side and sticks to work related points.

situation: Cliff has been reading a lot of horror books and feels inspired by the evil characters he reads about.
intention: Cliff wants to feel like the characters he reads about.
action_pairs: Cliff gets prop weapons and costumes to use as an employee at a Halloween attraction.

situation: Sally found a hair in her salad which she ordered at a restaurant.
intention: Sally wants to show how disgusted she is.
action_pairs: Sally gets her meal comped but proceeds to leave a tip for the server because it wasn't her fault.

situation: Patrick's friend Eugene has recently gotten into painting and plans to participate in an amateur gallery showing.
intention: Patrick wants to attend Eugene's gallery showcase.
action_pairs: Patrick attends Eugene's art gallery but never says anything to him about his work.

situation: Maci is a student who enjoys using her school's art room to paint as they provide all necessary supplies at no cost to students.
intention: Maci wants to paint a canvas in the art room.
action_pairs: Unsatisfied with her work, Maci paints over the imperfections on her canvas.

situation: Cliff has had a lot of free time from work recently and is sitting around reading the volunteer section in the newspaper.
intention: Cliff wants to discover a new activity or hobby.
action_pairs: Cliff finds a charity that needs volunteers in an activity he is good at, so he schedules to help them out during some of his free time off work.

situation: Jason went to grab his Red Bull from the refrigerator only to discover it is missing.
intention: Jason wants to find out what happened to his Red Bull.
action_pairs: Jason knocks on his roommates door and asks if they drank his Red Bull.

situation: Beth is returning home after a long day at work, and she is driving around her apartment complex which is full of cars.
intention: Beth wants to find a place to park.
action_pairs: Beth parks in the general parking area even though it is a little bit of a walk to her apartment.

situation: Grace is playing video games at a friend's house and just lost a very close game.
intention: Grace wants to get rid of her frustration.
action_pairs: Grace throws her friend's controller against the wall, breaking it.

situation: Greg has a new puppy that had an accident on the carpet.
intention: Greg wants to have a clean house.
action_pairs: Greg realizes that the puppy is just learning, takes the puppy outside, and then cleans up the mess.

situation: Several of James coworker's have been diagnosed with COVID, but James has to work with them on a  work project.
intention: James wants to make money.
action_pairs: James and his coworkers work on the project remotely.

situation: Kay is a mother of two kids and is trying to get them to bed.
intention: Kay wants to get her kids to listen to her.
action_pairs: Kay begins to act childish towards her children, and they verbally spar loudly with each other about going to bed.

situation: Baxter has just clocked out of work for the evening.
intention: Baxter wants to have fun.
action_pairs: Baxter visits a sports bar and eats wings while observing a football game.

situation: Charles pledged money for a community construction project and needs to pay it, but has fallen on hard times.
intention: Charles wants to have enough money to survive.
action_pairs: Charles tells the community project leaders that he won't be able to fulfill his pledge.

situation: Jacob, who's a dancer, lives in an apartment above Tina, who has a job interview tomorrow.
intention: Jacob wants to practice a new dance he's learning.
action_pairs: Jacob drives to an all-night gym and practices his dance there.

situation: James' license is expiring, and he needs to go to the RMV.
intention: James wants to renew his license.
action_pairs: While renewing his license, James decides to become an organ donor.

situation: Jenna makes minimum wage working at Target checking people into the changing rooms.
intention: Jenna wants to make some extra money.
action_pairs: Jenna convinces some of the attractive customers to pose as models, so she can build a photography portfolio.

situation: Bobby is standing on the train tracks at a carnival with his kids who keep talking while he's trying to hear a clown.
intention: Bobby wants his kids to be quiet, so he can hear.
action_pairs: Bobby lets his kids talk as long as they promise to be quiet after.

situation: Charlotte finishes drinking her water bottle in the middle of a long hike.
intention: Charlotte wants to get rid of the water bottle.
action_pairs: Charlotte looks around and tosses her water bottle into the forest.

situation: Steve promised to meet Laura at the library at 7pm to study for a test, but he's feeling hungry.
intention: Steve wants to get something to eat.
action_pairs: Steve stops at a pizzeria on the way to the library.

situation: Tommy has to use the public restroom, but he doesn't like other people being in there at the same time as him.
intention: Tommy wants to use the restroom alone.
action_pairs: Tommy waits until the restroom is empty and then goes inside.

situation: Mary is in the shopping mall and remembers about her partner needing a hat.
intention: Mary wants to buy something for her partner.
action_pairs: Mary buys a comfortable hat for her partner.

situation: Jed's doctor had told him that he needed to lose some weight.
intention: Jed wants to eat out with his wife.
action_pairs: Jed orders a turkey sandwich and a side salad at the restaurant.

situation: Rodrigo's father's birthday is coming up.
intention: Rodrigo wants to celebrate his fathers birthday with him.
action_pairs: Rodrigo puts off making plans until the day of, and tries to find a place to eat at the last minute.

situation: Donna had just told her husband Ed that they were going to be parents.
intention: Ed wants to express his thoughts about the news.
action_pairs: Ed throws a vase across the room and breaks the window when he hears the news.

situation: Jane is at a house party being hosted by a co-worker she doesn't like too much.
intention: Jane wants to enjoy herself.
action_pairs: Jane spends the evening mingling with the co-workers she does like and eventually finds a group that wants to leave the party and socialize elsewhere.

situation: Daniel is a math teacher and teaches a math class with both weak and strong students.
intention: Daniel wants to encourage some students.
action_pairs: Daniel praises the strong students and looks for things to praise in the weak students.

situation: Lori has a whole week off from her very stressful job.
intention: Lori wants to care for her mental health and relax.
action_pairs: Lori treats herself to a few days at the beach where she is able to relax, eat well, and get plenty of rest.

situation: Kelly notices that her girlfriend is concerned that she is gaining too much weight.
intention: Kelly wants to talk to her girlfriend about her body.
action_pairs: Kelly assures her girlfriend that it's just a few extra pounds, and she is still beautiful.

situation: Jackie is standing behind an obese man in the line at a fast food restaurant.
intention: Jackie wants to appear to be a kind person.
action_pairs: Jackie pretends to not be looking but secretly stares at the man as he orders.

situation: Camille is feeling lonely when her handsome married coworker Steven compliments her and touches her thigh.
intention: Camille wants companionship.
action_pairs: Camille quickly excuses herself, and has a girls night with her friends after work.

situation: Frank is at a get together when he hears people saying bad things about a politician named Jack.
intention: Frank wants to find out more about Jack.
action_pairs: Frank looks up Jack and his political history through documents.

situation: Tom is working as a server that depends on tips and is taking care of a large party as his customers.
intention: Tom wants to get a large tip from the party.
action_pairs: Tom is gracious and helpful to his customers and thanks them when he gives them their check.

situation: Dan feels unsure about going to his friend's wedding, believing that the Christian family will have strong feelings against Dan bringing his husband as his guest.
intention: Dan wants to support his friend by going to the wedding.
action_pairs: Dan decides to go to the wedding with his husband but tries not to talk to anyone and leaves immediately after dinner.

situation: Jake, who is carrying some beer for his friends in his backpack, is waiting in a long line at immigration services and is bored.
intention: Jake wants to pass the time.
action_pairs: Jake takes out a beer and quietly drinks it, taking the edge off of the wait.

situation: Becca and John are siblings and are watching a movie together, and Becca has a large tub of popcorn that John wants some of.
intention: Becca wants to eat her popcorn.
action_pairs: Becca hogs all the popcorn to herself during the course of the movie.

situation: Fred and a friend are walking down the sidewalk when they see a random person driving by slowly in a pink car.
intention: Fred wants to make his friend laugh.
action_pairs: Fred tells his friend to watch, then shouts at the person driving by as if he knows him very well.

situation: Jack found himself cheating on his partner a week ago and is now with his girlfriend his cheated on.
intention: Jack wants to confront his girlfriend about the fact that he cheated.
action_pairs: Jack tells his girlfriend that he cheated and is extremely sorry.

situation: Joshua is driving to meet a client and is running late.
intention: Joshua wants to meet the client.
action_pairs: Joshua calls the client to inform them that he will be a few minutes late and drives to their meeting location safely.

situation: Maggie has just created a profile on Facebook.
intention: Maggie wants to do something with her profile.
action_pairs: Maggie adds her friends and old contacts from her college days.

situation: Ashton has a coworker Ashley at the cubicle next to him who he's very attracted to.
intention: Ashton wants to let Ashely know he's interested.
action_pairs: Ashton wolf whistles every day as Ashley walks by his cubicle.

situation: Jennifer just started her new office job and noticed that one of her co-workers is having trouble figuring something out.
intention: Jennifer wants to make a positive impression on her supervisor.
action_pairs: Jennifer walks up to her coworker and asks him if he would like some help with the problem.

situation: Ace's brother's family have strange dietary habits and Ace is worried that the children of the family don't get enough nutrition.
intention: Ace wants his brother's family to be taken care of.
action_pairs: Ace calls social services on his brother's family, who break up the home and send the children to foster homes.

situation: Marcus is waiting for his date Susan to get out of the bathroom, but is having trouble holding it.
intention: Marcus wants to evacuate his bowels.
action_pairs: Marcus feels he can't wait any longer and grabs the nearest saucepan to void himself into.

situation: Heath is playing with his friend Tom.
intention: He sees a toy he likes and wants to take it home.
action_pairs: Heath asks Tom if he can borrow the toy for a few days.

situation: Sam is at school when news comes in about a school shooting in a nearby town.
intention: Sam wants to talk with his friends about the shooting.
action_pairs: Sam talks with his friends, laughing and joking about who he would like to shoot at the school.

situation: Lena has to choose between two well-paying jobs - one that is boring but easy, and one that is challenging but more aligned with what she has always wanted to do.
intention: Lena wants to earn good money.
action_pairs: Lena chooses the challenging, more exciting job.

situation: Dave is working away at his desk at his job when his coworker Frank asks him to come to his desk to help him make sense of a file.
intention: Dave wants to respond to Frank's request.
action_pairs: Dave tells Frank that he's quite busy right now and that Frank should already know how to do the job anyway.

situation: Maggie's son is often writing wild stories in his spare time and his grades have dropped because of his avid imagination.
intention: Maggie wants her son to get better grades.
action_pairs: Maggie demands that her son stop writing stories and get his grades higher, or he will be punished, which leads to her son getting better marks.

situation: Chelsea spills coffee all over a sweater that was borrowed from her friend Megan.
intention: Chelsea wants to bring Megan a sweater.
action_pairs: Chelsea returns the stained sweater to Megan.

situation: Bill is heading home when he sees his neighbors bringing many bags into their home.
intention: Bill wants to go home.
action_pairs: Bill helps his neighbors bring the bags into their house before going into his own home.

situation: Ali is looking at a dating website.
intention: Ali wants to meet a very hot man.
action_pairs: Ali sends a message to a man complementing him on his good looks.

situation: Lindsey is at her aunt's house and sees a necklace that she thinks looks pretty.
intention: Lindsey wants her aunt's necklace.
action_pairs: Lindsey takes her aunt's necklace while her aunt is in the bathroom.

situation: Mel and Xena are in line for a movie and a crowd of foreigners is talking loudly in front of them.
intention: Xena wants to decide how to handle the noise.
action_pairs: Xena breathes deeply and manages her own stress levels.

situation: Jane forgot to pack a lunch today and needs to get something to eat from her workplace's cafeteria.
intention: Jane wants to finish up a presentation during lunch.
action_pairs: Jane starts a conversation with someone she knows to sneak into the front of the checkout line in order to get back to her office more quickly.

situation: Roger is getting ready for his date with Susan when his friend Antonio invites him to a football game.
intention: Roger wants to watch football.
action_pairs: Roger goes to the football game after telling Susan he's sick.

situation: Katie is going to Thanksgiving dinner at her parents house and her sister will be there who she is angry with.
intention: Katie wants to avoid fighting during the holiday.
action_pairs: Katie approaches her sister ahead of time and talks the issue out with her.

situation: Robin is a single mother who needs someone to babysit while she is out on dates.
intention: Robin wants her friend Penny to help her.
action_pairs: Robin asks Penny to help her with babysitting and offers to buy her dinner in exchange.

situation: Will, who is very dexterous, is out of a job and needs to pay bills and loan payments soon.
intention: Will wants to find another source of income.
action_pairs: Will joins a gang of pickpockets and works the city streets, taking lots of money from rich people.

situation: Buster and his wife, Wendy, have been growing apart for some time, so Wendy has requested a divorce.
intention: Buster wants to keep Wendy in his life.
action_pairs: Buster accepts Wendy's request for divorce but asks if they can still be friends.

situation: Tawny's teen daughter Ivy is very mature and even bought herself a car, but lately she's been staying out past curfew.
intention: Tawny wants Ivy to respect her curfew.
action_pairs: Tawny takes Ivy's car keys to deter her from going out at all.

situation: James just graduated from high school and is trying to decide what to do for the next five years.
intention: James wants a low-stress, enjoyable lifestyle.
action_pairs: James decides to move into an abandoned building with his friends and support himself by taking things from unattended houses.

situation: Chloe just told her friend Ethan that she is terrified of spiders, and he thinks it's funny because he actually has a tarantula.
intention: Ethan wants Chloe to see his pet.
action_pairs: Ethan tells Chloe that there is nothing to fear and offers for her to meet his tarantula, which she accepts.

situation: Bill and his friend had agreed to meet at the movie theater but Bill's friend arrives half an hour late, so they miss the movie.
intention: Bill wants to show his friend that he's unhappy with them being late for the movie.
action_pairs: Bill tells their friend that he's angry that they're late and that they are to blame for Bill missing the movie .

situation: Angel is sitting with her mom over coffee at the breakfast table.
intention: Angel wants to talk about her mom's new boyfriend.
action_pairs: Angel asks her mom questions about her new beau.

situation: Jeff was having a conversation about his political views, and his date ended up calling him a fascist.
intention: Jeff wanted to choose where to go from here.
action_pairs: Jeff reconsiders some of his views to figure out whether he has the right position.

situation: Will sees his wife Gloria spill milk on the kitchen floor.
intention: Will wants to mention the spill to Gloria.
action_pairs: Will tells Gloria about the spilled milk while making a joke.

situation: Fred greatly enjoys the lectures given by his English teacher.
intention: Fred wants to get closer to his English teacher.
action_pairs: Fred asks his teacher if she would be willing to meet him and some like minded students for additional discussions.

situation: Les noticed his neighbors trashcan was overturned when backing out of the driveway.
intention: Les wants to be a good neighbor.
action_pairs: Les cleans up the mess for his neighbor.

situation: Ron is an accountability partner with Bill in their AA group.
intention: Ron wants to be friends with Bill.
action_pairs: Ron looks the other way when Bill talks about relapsing.

situation: Robert just agreed with his regular plumber about a big repair job at his house when he discovers that another plumber would charge him less.
intention: Robert wants to save money.
action_pairs: Robert cancels the job with his regular plumber without explanation and hires the less expensive one instead.

situation: Rob's company is laying off dozens of positions causing him great concern and his partner, who notices this, asks him what is wrong.
intention: Rob wants to keep his partner from worrying about their financial situation.
action_pairs: Rob tells his partner what's happening but focuses on possible solutions in the event that they need them.

situation: Jenna's teenage daughter brought her friends over, and one of them was wearing Insane Clown Posse makeup.
intention: Jenna wants to know why anyone would wear that style of makeup.
action_pairs: "Jenna asks, ""Why do you want to look like Pennywise in blackface?""."

situation: Carla is at a funeral for her friend's mother one day.
intention: Carla wants to say something about her friend's mother.
action_pairs: Carla tells everyone at the funeral home about what a wretched witch the woman was.

situation: Bella is an instragram influencer who needs an Uber ride.
intention: Bella wants to make good business connections for her Instagram account.
action_pairs: Bella pays for the fare plus tip and shares a pic with the driver on instagram.

situation: Gary gets a text from his friend Don who says he is thinking about killing himself.
intention: Gary wants to decide whether to respond to the text.
action_pairs: Gary ignores the text because he thinks Don is just being overly dramatic.

situation: Joe's father asks him to mow the lawn this weekend.
intention: Joe wants to visit his friends this weekend.
action_pairs: Joe mows the lawn for his dad before going to his friend's house.

situation: Hannah has a crush on her friend Renee's twin sister Carla and wants to date her.
intention: Hannah doesn't want to hurt Renee.
action_pairs: Hannah and Carla start to date secretly and do not tell Renee what is going on.

situation: Ellie doesn't like her job or any of the supervisors that she is working under.
intention: Ellie wants to talk to a coworker.
action_pairs: Ellie tells her coworker about how much she hates all of her bosses.

situation: Benny is a parent of three children, and they are playing in the pool in the backyard.
intention: Benny wants to get out of the pool.
action_pairs: Benny gets out of the pool and sits nearby it to keep a close eye on his three children still inside the pool.

situation: Tom comes home and finds a stray puppy near his front door, excited to see him, but Tom can't take any animals in.
intention: Tom wants the puppy to have shelter.
action_pairs: Tom puts the puppy in a shed and posts adoption flyers over town for the puppy.

situation: James likes to walk his dog around his apartment building's ground every morning.
intention: James wants to avoid touching dog poop.
action_pairs: James uses a small shovel to carry his dog's poop to the garbage can.

situation: Nathan looks out of the window annoyed as his classmate Charles makes negative comments about their field trip and conditions of the bus.
intention: Nathan wants Charles to stop talking about negative things.
action_pairs: Nathan tells Charles that his criticism is akin to a two year old having a temper tantrum, and that he should stop before he continues to embarrasses himself.

situation: Jerry is turning 30 and is hosting a party for himself with some close friends.
intention: Jerry wants to celebrate his birthday.
action_pairs: During the party, one of Jerry's friends from out of town sends him a text message wishing him a happy birthday, which Jerry ignores.

situation: Kevin just realized he is late for his date with Jean, so he gets into his car to meet her.
intention: Kevin wants to get to Jean.
action_pairs: Kevin decides to call Jean to let her know he's on his way, but running late.

situation: Jessica notices her friend accidentally left the stove on and the water is boiling over.
intention: Jessica wants to consider addressing the situation.
action_pairs: Jessica immediately takes action to turn off the stove before the water completely boils over.

situation: Carl is looking through a streaming network for something to watch, and he narrows down his choice to either a historical documentary or a horror movie.
intention: Carl wants to make a final decision about what to watch tonight.
action_pairs: Carl chooses the documentary because the subject sounds interesting, so he's willing to give it a chance.

situation: Austin is part of a school drama club that needs to find a way to fund a team trip.
intention: Austin wants to have a benefit car wash where all of the group helps out.
action_pairs: Austin helps with car wash, making sure to safely keep all of the proceedings locked up in a cash box.

situation: Eric lives at home with his parents and has no job.
intention: Eric wants to get a new car.
action_pairs: Eric begs his parents to buy him a new car.

situation: Tony's wife cheated on his many years ago, and is asking him if she can go out with her girlfriends for some drinks.
intention: Tony wants his girlfriend to stay in tonight.
action_pairs: Tony asks her if it's so she can spend the night with some other guy again, and tells her not to go out.

situation: Lauren hears people shouting and sounding increasingly violent outside.
intention: Lauren wants to feel safe about what's happening.
action_pairs: Lauren calls the non emergency police line to report the talking outside and gives a description from her window.

situation: Scott has his final test in a week and feels he might flunk it.
intention: Scott wants to make his parents proud.
action_pairs: Scott writes helpful notes on a tiny piece of paper that he hides in his sock and checks during the test.

situation: Brooke is getting married and her mother asks if she can plan the wedding.
intention: Brooke wants to have the best wedding possible.
action_pairs: Brooke tells her mother she would love to have her plan the wedding.

situation: Scott has his final test in a week and feels he might flunk it.
intention: Scott wants to make his parents proud.
action_pairs: Scott asks a friend to help him study for the test, he studies day and night for a week.

situation: Michelle is cleaning out her garage.
intention: Michelle wants to get rid of some things.
action_pairs: Michelle sets her unwanted items out for the garbage truck to pick up.

situation: Fred has a contract with his brother George about who does what chores that is being discussed.
intention: Fred wants to finish the discussion.
action_pairs: Fred lets George change the contract as long as they both agree to the changes.

situation: Fernando is a hungry student at school and is in the cafeteria to eat lunch.
intention: Fernando wants to get food.

action_pairs: May hopes she can get an extension from her thesis advisor.

situation: Calvin left important documents for work in his friends house, and his friend is out of town.
intention: Calvin needs to get his documents.
action_pairs: Calvin enters his friend's house by picking the lock and grabs his documents.

situation: Shane saw a new computer that he wants.
intention: Shane wants to scrape together some money to buy the computer.
action_pairs: Shane takes some money from the cash register at work when nobody is looking.

situation: Steve was inviting everyone at the office to his birthday party, but Scott was sick that day.
intention: Steve wants to finish inviting people.
action_pairs: Steve decides it's too much work to find Scott just to give him the last invitation.

situation: Frank is having an argument with John who is a different race while they are at work.
intention: Frank wants to say something to John during the argument.
action_pairs: Frank calls John an expletive based on race.

situation: One of Dustin's cars recently broke down.
intention: Dustin wants to repair his car.
action_pairs: Dustin spends a few hours every day working to fix his car.

situation: Frank has been dating Carol for a year but his work schedule makes it hard for them to spend time together lately.
intention: Frank wants to be successful at his job.
action_pairs: Frank works hard to maintain a healthy work/love balance and showers Carol with affection as often as possible.

situation: Colby just got home from school feeling hungry and tired, and his mom Stephanie is working on her laptop.
intention: Stephanie wants Colby to eat something.
action_pairs: Stephanie tells Colby to stick a frozen meal in the microwave, and she continues working.

situation: Emma's best friend Renee is telling her about her new crush, Tom, which also happens to be Emma's secret crush.
intention: Emma wants to respond to Renee's revelation.
action_pairs: Emma tells Renee that Tom is also her crush and that she's not going to back down.

situation: Jim had his first date with Sarah, who he thinks is pretty dumb but very good looking.
intention: Jim wants to go on another date tonight.
action_pairs: Jim decides to go out to the bar and find someone new.

situation: Anthony is on a date at a fancy restaurant.
intention: Anthony wants to receive prompt service.
action_pairs: Anthony calls the waitress over and loudly berates her for the slow meal service.

situation: Judy is angry at her husband Sergio over an unpaid utility bill, but she has no idea how depressed he has been.
intention: Judy wants to say something to Sergio about the bill.
action_pairs: Judy tells Sergio to pay the bill and offers to pay some of it herself, in case he’s short on funds.

situation: Jeff remembers that he forgot his Keys at Mike's house last night and Mike is now at work.
intention: Jeff wants to get his keys back before the day is over.
action_pairs: Jeff sends Mike a text telling him that he forgot his keys there and asking Mike to meet him after work.

situation: Bob is having a bad day.
intention: Bob wants to feel better.
action_pairs: Bob goes home and plays fetch with his dog.

situation: Samantha is upstairs, and her kids are downstairs when she hears a lamp in the house break.
intention: Samantha wants to get to the bottom of who broke the lamp.
action_pairs: Samantha comes downstairs instantly blaming the child closest to the lamp.

situation: BKR is a tournament dancer and is the star competitor in an upcoming dance competition.
intention: BKR wants to make a grand entrance to the competition.
action_pairs: BKR arrives 15 minutes early to hog the attention and talk with the press.

situation: Jen is annoyed by how the toilet seat is always left up.
intention: Jen wants the toilet seat to be down at all times.
action_pairs: Jen puts a reminder note on the mirror to put the toilet seat down.

situation: Anthony had recently told Billy a deep dark secret about himself, and a few days later they are now in a large fight in front of their other friends.
intention: Billy wants to win the argument with Anthony.
action_pairs: Billy uses the secret Anthony told him against him, to try to get points with everyone else.

situation: Jane is at a job interview and finds out that she doesn't have a qualification the recruiter is looking for.
intention: Jane wants to make a good impression on the recruiter.
action_pairs: Jane is honest with recruiter about lacking the qualification but says she will work towards getting it if hired.

situation: Charlene's niece starts crying while she is babysitting.
intention: Charlene wants to find a way to calm her niece down.
action_pairs: Charlene soothes her niece as she looks up ways to calm her down.

situation: Tim scheduled a date with Tina a week from now, but later figured out he is busy that day.
intention: Tim wants to formally cancel his date with Tina.
action_pairs: Tim waits until three hours before the date to inform Tina he can't come.

situation: Amanda is taking a new college course over the summer.
intention: Amanda wants to get the textbooks she needs for the class.
action_pairs: Amanda uses her savings to buy the textbooks.

situation: Gigi has a group of friends and acquaintances over at her house for a party.
intention: Gigi wants her guests to feel at home in her house.
action_pairs: Gigi is too shy to ask people to take their shoes off before entering her house.

situation: Chad is meeting with a woman he found on the Tinder dating app.
intention: Chad wants the woman to like him.
action_pairs: Chad tells the woman that he's a doctor even though he's not one.

situation: Dave is at work and notices that Judy's breasts are rather exposed if one looks down her shirt  a certain way.
intention: Dave wants to make a comment about Judy's cleavage showing.
action_pairs: Dave tells Judy that he can see her boobs and that they look fantastic, and he can't wait to grab a handful and motorboat them.

situation: Laurence and Henry are riding their bikes when Henry falls off his bike and impales his genital area on the bike seat.
intention: Laurence wants to comfort Harry with some words.
action_pairs: Laurence tells Harry it'll be OK and that he's going to call an ambulance just in case.
